# Linear Algebra for Quantitative Finance

Linear algebra plays a central role in many modern fields, including 
artificial intelligence, machine learning, and deep learning.
About 40 years ago, students were required to study abstract algebra 
before approaching linear algebra — the subject was treated as a 
formal, proof-heavy discipline. Today, it is taught much more 
concretely, driven by computational needs and real-world applications.

This note covers linear algebra from the ground up — starting from 
vectors and matrices, through eigenvalues and decompositions (LU, QR, SVD), 
numerical techniques, and culminating in PCA — with a focus on how 
these tools are applied in quantitative finance.

## Contents
1. Vectors & Vector Spaces 向量与向量空间
2. Matrices & Matrix Operations 矩阵与矩阵运算
3. Eigenvalues & Eigenvectors 特征值与特征向量
4. Matrix Decompositions 矩阵分解
   - LU Decomposition
   - QR Decomposition
   - Singular Value Decomposition (SVD)
5. Numerical Methods 数值方法
6. Principal Component Analysis (PCA) 主成分分析
7. Applications in Quant Finance 在量化金融中的应用
   - Covariance Matrix & Risk 协方差矩阵与风险
   - Factor Models 因子模型
   - Portfolio Optimization 投资组合优化
